ns0:Concept.displayName: Single liveborn infant, delivered by cesarean

ns0:DescribedValueSet.ns0:Purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains types of delivery that represent the single live birth delivered cesarean section.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who delivered single live newborn by cesarean section. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Diagnosis" category or the attribute of "Diagnoses" for the Encounter category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Include ICD-10-CM codes that identify patients who delivered single live newborn by cesarean section.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.)
